		<section class="hpcontainer" id="news_container"><header><h1><a href="/apps/news/">News and Announcements</a></h1></header><section id="homepage_news_list" class="homepage-news-list" aria-label="Newslist"><article id="hp_news_article_1" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_1_title">
		<a href="/apps/news/article/1210635">
								NUSD and Distance Learning Spring 2020
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_1_title"><p>
								Thank you parents and family members for your support of our Distance Learning programs!  The past month has brought many changes in our District.  Please make sure that your child uses his/her District email to contact his/her teacher if he/she has not contacted the teacher yet.  In order to best serve the needs of our students, we are working on our grading system for this semester to ensure that students are not harmed by the change in programs. If your child is having difficulty with homework, please contact teachers and/or principal for support.  <br><br>Also, the District has started checking out laptops and will also have wifi devices available for check-out next week to ensure that ALL students can participate in our online meetings, assignments and curriculum.  Make sure and let your principal know if you need a laptop or a wifi hotspot as soon as possible.   <br><br>Look for the NUSD School Newsletter later this week on our websites.
							</p>
						</section></article><article id="hp_news_article_2" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_2_title">
		<a href="/apps/news/article/1209330">
								Chemehuevi School Grab and Go Meals for All Grade Levels Tuesday 4/14 9:00-10:00
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_2_title"><p>
								All students living in the Chemehuevi/Havasu Landing area may pick up 5 days of meals on Tuesday 4/14 from 9:00-10:00.  Student work for all students may be dropped off at that time.
							</p>
						</section></article><article id="hp_news_article_3" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_3_title">
		<a href="/apps/news/article/1209327">
								Student Work Drop Off at District Office Monday/Tuesday/Thursday 8:30-1:30
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_3_title"><p>
								Boxes are available outside of the District Office (back door) to drop off student work.  Make sure your child's name is on their work.  Make sure and wear a mask and stand at least 6 feet apart.
							</p>
						</section></article><article id="hp_news_article_4" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_4_title">
		<a href="/apps/news/article/1209326">
								Grab and Go Meals Tuesday April 14th from 11:00-1:00 for Needles' Sites
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_4_title"><p>
								Grab and Go Meals will be provided on Tuesday, April 14th. Meals for NHS, NMS, and ETC  will be available in the high school parking lot.  Meals for Vista will be available in the Vista Circle.  Headstart will provide meals for preschool families.  CDS may pick up at NHS or NMS.
							</p>
						</section></article><article id="hp_news_article_5" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_5_title">
		<a href="/apps/news/article/1208063">
								Where to Find Student Assignments for NMS and NHS
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_5_title"><p>
								These schedules direct you to the NMS and NHS websites where students can find their assignments and information on live classes with teachers.
							</p>
						</section></article><article id="hp_news_article_6" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_6_title">
		<a href="/apps/news/article/1207074">
								District Office Hours
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_6_title"><p>
								The District Office will be open on Monday, Tuesday and Thursday from 8:30-1:30.  Work may be dropped off at this time and placed in the drawers outside of the back door.  Drawers are identified by school site.
							</p>
						</section></article><article id="hp_news_article_7" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_7_title">
		<a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prevent-getting-sick/diy-cloth-face-coverings.html">
								Face Masks Now Required Anytime Outside of the Home (click here)
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_7_title"><p>
								As of April 7th, it is now MANDATORY to wear a face mask anytime one leaves their home.  Face masks can be made at home with clothes, towels, pillow cases, bags with no-sew and sewing methods! See the information on the attached link from the CDC.
							</p>
						</section></article><article id="hp_news_article_8" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_8_title">
		<a href="/apps/news/article/1206042">
								Vista Grab and Go Meals and Student Work on April 7th 11:00-1:00
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_8_title"><p>
								Vista Grab and Go Meals will be available today from 11:00-1:00 in the NHS parking lot at the first station under the shade structure.  Student work packets will be available in the Vista Circle from 11:00-12:00.  We are trying to ease the congestion by offering 2 locations.   This  will be the last week for work packet distribution during Grab and Go Meals.  After this time, meals will be every Tuesday from 11:00-12:00 and work assignments will be distributed by teachers online. If online is not available for students, then the packets will be mailed home until the District can provide wifi connectivity for these students.
							</p>
						</section></article><article id="hp_news_article_9" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_9_title">
		<a href="/apps/news/article/1205992">
								NMS/NHS Student Work Packet Distribution April 7th 11:00-1:00
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_9_title"><p>
								NMS and NHS students may pick up hard copy packets at 2 separate locations by school in the parking lot if they do not have online access.   Student work will be collected at this time and future drop offs will be available at meal distributions on Tuesdays from 11:00-1:00 and also in black boxes outside the district office. All middle school and high school student work is available on each school's website by classes and teacher. This will be the last generic distribution of work packets as assignments will be online or mailed home to those without online access at this time. The district is working to establish online access for all.  Stay well!
							</p>
						</section></article><article id="hp_news_article_10" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_10_title">
		<a href="/apps/news/article/1205984">
								Grab and Go Meals for Tuesday, April 7th
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_10_title"><p>
								This is the Needles Unified School District with a message on Grab and Go Meals and work packets for Tuesday, April 7th between 11:00 and 1:00.  Grab and Go Meals will include 5 days of food and will be available in the high school parking lot under the shade shed as you enter and at Needles Head Start.  Grab and Go Meals will be available every Tuesday from 11:00-1:00 for the remainder of the school year.  Be well!
							</p>
						</section></article><a href="/apps/news/category/5463" class="read-more-link">Show All News »</a>

	</section></section>
